usage:
    lolcat --version
    lolcat run [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    lolcat fmt [--check] [<file-or-dir> ...]
    lolcat compile [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile> [-o <output>]
    lolcat genpkg[:backend] [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile> [out]
    lolcat check [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <srcfile>
    lolcat checkpkg [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    lolcat lex [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <srcfile>
    lolcat ast [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <srcfile>
    lolcat mir [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    lolcat --version
    lolcat --help

<target> is one of: cli-libc (default), cli-eval, wasm-min, playbit
`hop run` defaults to cli-eval when --platform is omitted
